==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: suricate
<hw>su"ri*cate</hw></mhw>
<pr>(s⟦umac⟧"r⟦icr⟧*k⟦acr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>surikate</ets>, from the native name in South Africa.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A South African mongooselike viverrine
(<spn>Suricata suricatta</spn> or <spn>Suricata tetradactyla</spn>)
having a lemurlike face and only four toes; called also
<altname>mierkat</altname>, <altname>yellow mongoose</altname> and
<altname>zenick</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>surikate</asp>.]</altsp> <note>The animal called <er>zenick</er>
seems also to be related to or identical to the mierkat, but no
reference can be found on the internet.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> meerkat.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Surinam toad</ent>⟦br⟧
